<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>5. Dropping Spans on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector-old/5-dropping-spans/</link><description>Recent content in 5. Dropping Spans on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector-old/5-dropping-spans/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>5.1 Configuration</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector-old/5-dropping-spans/5-1-configuration/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector-old/5-dropping-spans/5-1-configuration/</guid><description>&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Switch to your &lt;strong&gt;Gateway terminal&lt;/strong&gt; window and open the &lt;code&gt;gateway.yaml&lt;/code&gt; file. Update the &lt;code&gt;processors&lt;/code&gt; section with the following configuration:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Add a &lt;code&gt;filter&lt;/code&gt; processor&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;br&gt;
Configure the gateway to exclude spans with the name &lt;code&gt;/_healthz&lt;/code&gt;. The &lt;code&gt;error_mode: ignore&lt;/code&gt; directive ensures that any errors encountered during filtering are ignored, allowing the pipeline to continue running smoothly. The &lt;code&gt;traces&lt;/code&gt; section defines the filtering rules, specifically targeting spans named &lt;code&gt;/_healthz&lt;/code&gt; for exclusion.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>5.2 Test Filter Processor</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector-old/5-dropping-spans/5-2-test-filter/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector-old/5-dropping-spans/5-2-test-filter/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;To test your configuration, you&amp;rsquo;ll need to generate some trace data that includes a span named &lt;code&gt;&amp;quot;/_healthz&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Start the Gateway&lt;/strong&gt;: In your &lt;strong&gt;Gateway terminal&lt;/strong&gt; window start the &lt;code&gt;gateway&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;../otelcol --config ./gateway.yaml&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Start the Agent&lt;/strong&gt;: In your &lt;strong&gt;Agent terminal&lt;/strong&gt; window start the &lt;code&gt;agent&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;../otelcol --config ./agent.yaml&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Start the Loadgen&lt;/strong&gt;: In the &lt;strong&gt;Spans terminal&lt;/strong&gt; window run the &lt;code&gt;loadgen&lt;/code&gt; with the flag to also send &lt;code&gt;healthz&lt;/code&gt; spans along with base spans:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>